#. <section class="sutta" id="sn7.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.17:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Upāsakavagga"
msgstr "2. Lay Followers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Navakammikasutta"
msgstr "17. The Builder"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.180"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.387"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.17:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain "
"forest grove."

# In this sutta I use jungle for vana to (hopefully) bring out the puns
msgctxt "sn7.17:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena navakammikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe "
"kammantaṃ kārāpeti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Builder was doing some building "
"work in that jungle thicket."

msgctxt "sn7.17:1.3"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho navakammikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ aññatarasmiṃ "
"sālarukkhamūle nisinnaṃ pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ "
"satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"He saw the Buddha sitting down cross-legged at the root of a certain sal "
"tree, with his body straight, and mindfulness established right there."

msgctxt "sn7.17:1.4"
msgid "Disvānassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Seeing this, it occurred to him:"

msgctxt "sn7.17:1.5"
msgid "“ahaṃ kho imasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe kammantaṃ kārāpento ramāmi."
msgstr "“I enjoy doing this building work here in the jungle."

msgctxt "sn7.17:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ samaṇo gotamo kiṃ kārāpento ramatī”ti?"
msgstr "I wonder what the ascetic Gotama enjoys doing?”"

msgctxt "sn7.17:1.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho navakammikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami. "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Bhāradvāja the Builder went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.17:2.1"
msgid "“Ke nu kammantā karīyanti,"
msgstr "“What kind of work do you do"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:2.2"
msgid "bhikkhu sālavane tava;"
msgstr "as a mendicant in the sal jungle?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:2.3"
msgid "Yadekako araññasmiṃ,"
msgstr "How do you find enjoyment"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:2.4"
msgid "ratiṃ vindati gotamo”ti."
msgstr "alone in the wilderness, Gotama?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.17:3.1"
msgid "“Na me vanasmiṃ karaṇīyamatthi,"
msgstr "“There’s nothing I need to do in the jungle;"

# Accepting visukkham, see BB’s note. This is, in addition, supported by SA2 96, which has 一切盡枯摧
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:3.2"
msgid "Ucchinnamūlaṃ me vanaṃ visūkaṃ;"
msgstr "my jungle’s cut down at the root, it’s withered away."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:3.3"
msgid "Svāhaṃ vane nibbanatho visallo,"
msgstr "With jungle cleared and free of thorns,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.17:3.4"
msgid "Eko rame aratiṃ vippahāyā”ti."
msgstr "I enjoy being alone in the jungle, having given up discontent.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.388"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.17:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, navakammikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Builder said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn7.17:4.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …"
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama …"

msgctxt "sn7.17:4.3"
msgid ""
"upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"
